==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin '''[[caelibatus]]''', perfect passive participle of '''[[caelibare]]''', from '''[[caelebs]]''', ''[[unmarried]]''

===Noun===
'''celibacy''' (uncountable)

# {{archaic}}: The state of not being married.
# Abstaining from sexual relations.

